Title: Was That Really Me?: How Everyday Stress Brings Out Our Hidden Personality

Author: Noami Quenk
Publisher: Quercus
Publication date: 08/13/2002
ISBN13: 9780891061700
ISBN10: 0891061703


Summary
-------
Psychologist Naomi Quenk further explores what we keep hidden within and only reveal when we are stressed.


Description
-----------
Psychologist Naomi Quenk discusses the stress patterns that various personality types experience. Using Jungian psychological type theory and the MBTIÂ© personality inventory, Quenk helps readers turn their moments of stress into gems of personal understanding and growth. Work-related stress and the effects of stress over time are both explored in Was That Really Me?, as is a simple explanation of type dynamics, type differentiation, and type development. Including discussions of how each of the sixteen personality types functions at work and what each finds stressful or energizing, plus new stories about people in the grip of their inferior functions, Was That Really Me? helps readers learn from moments of stress
